title: Gary Kubiak gives his thoughts on benching Peyton Manning
text:
Gary Kubiak gives his thoughts on benching Peyton Manning NESN 9 hrs ago Pat Bradley © AAron Ontiveroz / Getty Images Gary Kubiak doesn't believe that it is time to sit quarterback Peyton Manning yet. Peyton Manning has looked more bad than good this season, leading many wondering whether it's time for the 39-year-old to hang up the cleats.
AdChoices Reporters in Denver were blunt with Denver Broncos coach Gary Kubiak, asking him outright whether backup quarterback Brock Osweiler should get the start.
Gary Kubiak asked if it is time to play Brock Osweiler. "No. Peyton is doing just fine."
— Lindsay Jones (@bylindsayhjones) October 12, 2015 Sounds like Kubiak has made his decision.
Of course, if Manning continues his horrid interception pace (six touchdowns, seven interceptions), there won’t be much of a decision to make.
